Download the package.
Open the php.ini temp buffer and error fix file and copy it.
Open your php.ini file in your phpmyadmin under settings.
Paste the copied text over your old php.ini file and save it. 
Restart and your website will work.

If you don't want to change the whole php.ini file in your sql, 
copy and paste
error_reporting = E_ALL ^ E_DEPRECATED
over your error reporting = (what it says now)
and change your 
output_buffering = Off
to
output_buffering = On
and save the file.

*This will too be deprecated soon I hear. 
**This is only a temp fix.
